headline: This Magnificent Artificial Intelligence (AI) Stock Has Crashed 12%. Here's Why That's Great News for Investors
summary: Dell Technologies' (NYSE: DELL) remarkable stock market rally came to a halt after the company released fiscal 2025 third-quarter results (for the three months ended Nov. 1) on Nov. 26, with shares of the technology giant that's known for its personal computer (PC) and server solutions dropping more than 12% in a single day.  It wasn't surprising to see investors pressing the panic button following Dell's results.  Dell reported fiscal third-quarter revenue of $24.4 billion, an increase of 10% from the year-ago quarter.
